This is a pong game developed for chipKIT UNO 32 with a basic IO shield.
To compile and run the game, open MCB32Tools, navigate to the correct directory, 
type make and then make install with the chipkit connected. The game will boot
instantly and a splash screen will appear that can be dismissed with any button
to enter the game menu.

The game contains the following source files:

main.c:
	Contains the logic for the game and game menus

display.c:
	Contains logic for writing to and updating the display

IOinit.c:
	Contains logic for initializing IO for screen, buttons, timers and leds

inputs.c
	Contains logic for detecting button presses

vectors.S:
	Contains the interrupt handler and the exception handler

stubs.c:
	Contains stubs for functions run during micro controller
	initialization
